{"info": {"author": "Shyam Dwaraknath", "author_email": "shyamd@lbl.gov", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "[![testing](https://github.com/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/workflows/testing/badge.svg)](https://github.com/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/actions?query=workflow%3Atesting)\n[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex)\n[![Language grade: Python](https://img.shields.io/lgtm/grade/python/g/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex.svg?logo=lgtm&logoWidth=18)](https://lgtm.com/projects/g/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/context:python)\n\n# mkdocs-bibtex\n\nA [MkDocs](https://www.mkdocs.org/) plugin for citation management using bibtex.\n\n## Setup\n\nInstall the plugin using pip:\n\n```\npip install mkdocs-bibtex\n```\n\nNext, add the following lines to your `mkdocs.yml`:\n\n```yml\nplugins:\n  - search\n  - bibtex:\n      bib_file: \"refs.bib\"\n      cite_style: \"pandoc\"\n```\n\n> If you have no `plugins` entry in your config file yet, you'll likely also want to add the `search` plugin. MkDocs enables it by default if there is no `plugins` entry set.\n\n## Options\n\n- `bib_file` - Name of your bibtex file. Either the absolute path or the path relative to `mkdocs.yml`\n- `bib_dir` - Directory for bibtex files to load, same as above for path resolution\n- `cite_style` - The way you place citations into text: \"pandoc\" for `[@myRef]` and \"plain\" for `@myRef`\n- `bib_command` - The command for your bibliography, defaults to `\\bibliography`\n- `full_bib_command` - The command for your bibliography, defaults to `\\full_bibliography`\n\n## Usage\n\nIn your markdown files:\n\n1. Add your citations as you would normally using either \"plain\" or \"pandoc\" style\n2. Add in `\\bibliography` or whatever you set your `bib_command` to where you want your references.\n3. Add in `\\full_bibliography` or whatever you set your `full_bib_command` to where you want the full set of references. *Note*: This is not guaranteed to work yet since one issue is the order in which markdown files are processed. Might need to do something using the `on_files()` event first.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/", "keywords": "mkdocs python markdown bibtex", "license": "BSD-3-Clause-LBNL", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "mkdocs-bibtex", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mkdocs-bibtex/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mkdocs-bibtex/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mkdocs-bibtex/0.2.3/", "requires_dist": ["mkdocs (>=1)", "markdown (>=3.1.1)", "pybtex (>=0.22)"], "requires_python": ">=3.5", "summary": "An MkDocs plugin that enables managing citations with BibTex", "version": "0.2.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p><a href=\"https://github.com/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/actions?query=workflow%3Atesting\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"testing\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/04ecbc87cf9e89d696a68f45165ccca6fd8bd364/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f736879616d642f6d6b646f63732d6269627465782f776f726b666c6f77732f74657374696e672f62616467652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://codecov.io/gh/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"codecov\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/04718c0973f3460d765f551d535f6f784fc8b955/68747470733a2f2f636f6465636f762e696f2f67682f736879616d642f6d6b646f63732d6269627465782f6272616e63682f6d61737465722f67726170682f62616467652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://lgtm.com/projects/g/shyamd/mkdocs-bibtex/context:python\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Language grade: Python\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/a0b38d1e09553a2d50f71e41b610a14ed19aac82/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f6c67746d2f67726164652f707974686f6e2f672f736879616d642f6d6b646f63732d6269627465782e7376673f6c6f676f3d6c67746d266c6f676f57696474683d3138\"></a></p>\n<h1>mkdocs-bibtex</h1>\n<p>A <a href=\"https://www.mkdocs.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">MkDocs</a> plugin for citation management using bibtex.</p>\n<h2>Setup</h2>\n<p>Install the plugin using pip:</p>\n<pre><code>pip install mkdocs-bibtex\n</code></pre>\n<p>Next, add the following lines to your <code>mkdocs.yml</code>:</p>\n<pre>plugins:\n  - search\n  - bibtex:\n      bib_file: \"refs.bib\"\n      cite_style: \"pandoc\"\n</pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you have no <code>plugins</code> entry in your config file yet, you'll likely also want to add the <code>search</code> plugin. MkDocs enables it by default if there is no <code>plugins</code> entry set.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Options</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><code>bib_file</code> - Name of your bibtex file. Either the absolute path or the path relative to <code>mkdocs.yml</code></li>\n<li><code>bib_dir</code> - Directory for bibtex files to load, same as above for path resolution</li>\n<li><code>cite_style</code> - The way you place citations into text: \"pandoc\" for <code>[@myRef]</code> and \"plain\" for <code>@myRef</code></li>\n<li><code>bib_command</code> - The command for your bibliography, defaults to <code>\\bibliography</code></li>\n<li><code>full_bib_command</code> - The command for your bibliography, defaults to <code>\\full_bibliography</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>In your markdown files:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Add your citations as you would normally using either \"plain\" or \"pandoc\" style</li>\n<li>Add in <code>\\bibliography</code> or whatever you set your <code>bib_command</code> to where you want your references.</li>\n<li>Add in <code>\\full_bibliography</code> or whatever you set your <code>full_bib_command</code> to where you want the full set of references. <em>Note</em>: This is not guaranteed to work yet since one issue is the order in which markdown files are processed. Might need to do something using the <code>on_files()</code> event first.</li>\n</ol>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6766127, "releases": {"0.2.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "fe01347608a701acc92b183e31df65f6", "sha256": "910b27b09b04eb8722d6c2265fcd2e89fb9cf8803eaf6054876db33864b781bb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "mkdocs_bibtex-0.2.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "fe01347608a701acc92b183e31df65f6", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7", "size": 5893, "upload_time": "2019-06-28T00:59:24", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-06-28T00:59:24.132219Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/65/fa/7e2d571e90b9213e302f1b635b2db95f0e8a212e5a16aca55caa7c57e2f6/mkdocs_bibtex-0.2.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "cd41cb7fc3dce4785353d22dfcce647e", "sha256": "ee855f2e8b79f1d88908a9e1eb9f97f816ce97c7e9e0fce0bead0405416a1a8c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "mkdocs-bibtex-0.2.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "cd41cb7fc3dce4785353d22dfcce647e", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.7", "size": 4054, "upload_time": "2019-06-28T00:59:26", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-06-28T00:59:26.359031Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/b7/9e/3ba7b1eaa68a0ba8306e7ddda1c31ae216ad8d474146bcb1fd415e5013a1/mkdocs-bibtex-0.2.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.2.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "d7f55d20e00907effb4279ee375fb5b2", "sha256": "878d3c4fb625052b8b1c9a7e746648af43c9f0735a1794fe31971a9b122c6e2f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "mkdocs_bibtex-0.2.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "d7f55d20e00907effb4279ee375fb5b2", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 5890, "upload_time": "2019-06-28T16:23:17", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-06-28T16:23:17.435433Z", "url":